The paper deals with channel estimation and interference cancellation techniques in the context of satellite communications, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of iterative decoding and modulation techniques, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an improved estimation technique that combines different methods, which can be considered as a data science (cs.DS) approach.
